title: Emergency Social Services: Social Worker
stext: Emergency Social Services is to provide emergency one-time citizens of the elderly and disabled people in dire need of social support. It may include the following social services: 1) a one-time provision in desperate need free hot meals and food packages; 2) provision of clothing, shoes and other essentials; 3) one-off material assistance; 4) assistance in obtaining temporary accommodation; 5) The organization of legal aid in order to protect the rights of people served; 6) the organization of emergency medical and psychological care, involving for this work of psychologists and the clergy and the allocation for the purpose of additional phone numbers; 7) other urgent social services.
